<TEXT>
when nelson mandela dignified but fists 
clenched high in exultation walked out of south africas victor 
verster prison the major us networks and cnn and south african 
tv aired it live 
the dramatic moment doubtless was taken for granted by younger 
viewers used to instant tv newsby satellite in the slow old days 
the moment would be shot on film and wouldnt reach the us for 
hours or maybe a day 
still its how you tell the story that counts not how you show 
off your technosmarts 
and on that basis abcs coverage of the mandela story this 
weekend was easily the best in all respects in reporting the 
story in giving it perspective and in showing with a minimum of 
extraneous chatter the drama of the moments before during and 
after mandelas release 
ted koppel who went to south africa last monday and on 
wednesday anchored the first of three nightline broadcasts 
there smoothly and knowledgeably anchored abcs sunday coverage 
from cape town 
nbc anchorman tom brokaw he and koppel were the only us 
network anchors at saturdays news conference in which president 
fw de klerk said mandela would be freed also was in that city 
on sunday 
neither was physically present at the deceptively 
pleasantlooking prison grounds for the release however they 
worked from other locations while cbs anchorman dan rather worked 
out of johannesburg more than 800 miles away 
sundays live pictures from the prison entrance and the crowd 
and security police around it were provided on a pooled basis by 
the staterun south african broadcasting corp 
koppel and abc wisely concentrated on scenes of the prison 
entrance and the crowds there showing the long wait the patience 
of those come to see a man imprisoned 27 years ago for choosing to 
fight apartheid 
brokaw and rather on the other hand tended to fill the wait 
with interviews of various south african figures going more for 
the analytical than the personalall that was well and good 
journalistically speaking 
but given the drama of main event at hand it came across as 
awfully dry stuff 
abc and nbc also broadcast portions of the lowkey 
straightforward running commentary of sabc announcer clarence 
keyter which gave us viewers a sense of what kind of coverage 
south africans were getting on staterun tv 
all the networks had crews in soweto televising the reactions 
of a crowd of joyous blacks in front of mandelas home there 
but abc in a literal case of oneupsmanship also had a 
chartered helicopter flying over the area showing the scene from 
the air giving viewers an idea of the size of the crowd which 
seemed to fill perhaps two blocks 
this may be an era of the portable anchor but the story proved 
a longdistance scramble for rather and to a lesser extent 
brokaw 
brokaw in new york when nbc was tipped that mandela might be 
released this weekend made a mad dash for the airport thursday and 
flew to south africa a spokeswoman said 
rathers trip was just as hurried but far longer after more 
than a week of anchoring from moscow he had returned on friday to 
new york a spokeswoman said but he roared right out again 
saturday morning to johannesburg 
only abc anchorman peter jennings was able to rest at home here 
but he had a few air miles logged too according to a spokesman 
jennings after a week in cambodia working on a special flew to 
moscow last week to anchor part of world news tonight from 
monday through wednesday then he returned here 
he wouldnt have found abc news president roone arledge here 
though a spokesman said arledge had flown to south africa to help 
direct abcs coverage 
