the government says ford drew more than 1 million in loans from 
butcher banks though the amount of money the congressman allegedly 
received is unclear since some loans outlined in the indictment 
apparently were used to pay off others 
ford a democrat and tennessees first and only black member of 
congress is credited with running a political machine that can 
deliver the black vote in memphis he is accused of selling that 
influence to the butchers for their political and business gain 
he has faced little or no opposition for his 9th congressional 
district seat since he was first elected to congress in 1974 
ford charged with conspiracy bank and mail fraud could be 
sent to prison for up to 95 years if convicted on all 19 counts 
against him 
the trial is expected to last as long as two months 
the butcher brothers once controlled a business empire that 
included some 40 banks and savings and loans but both are now 
serving 20year prison sentences for bank fraud 
ch butcher jr has pleaded guilty to two counts in the ford 
indictment 
jake butcher who ran unsuccessfully for governor of tennessee 
in 1974 and 1978 was listed as an unindicted coconspirator in the 
ford indictment 
ford has argued since his indictment that racism and politics 
are behind his legal troubles that he was indicted by a grand jury 
in knoxville rather than memphis because eastern tennessee is 
heavily republican and primarily white memphis fords hometown 
is 50 percent black 
ford failed to carry that argument in pretrial motions and the 
6th us circuit court of appeals in cincinnati refused to consider 
it before trial 
the trial was moved to memphis from knoxville at fords request 
fords codefendants are accountant david crabtree and lawyers 
douglas beaty and karl schledwitz they are all charged with bank 
fraud and mail fraud conspiracy in addition schledwitz and beaty 
face 15 counts of mail fraud and crabtree is charged in four mail 
fraud counts 
</TEXT>
