<TEXT>
a massive 2inchthick blanket 
of crude oil spilled by the tanker american trader moved ashore 
today invading a 2mile stretch of beach near an environmentally 
sensitive wildlife refuge 
a 200member cleanup crew was dispatched to the fouled beach 
before dawn in an effort to mop up the black goo in what 
authorities called the most serious beach pollution since the 
400000gallon spill last wednesday 
we got hit with more oil overnight than we have in this whole 
process we got the biggest hit at bolsa chica state beach said 
tony kozlowski spokesman for the cleanup coordinators british 
petroleum which chartered the tanker 
the wildlife refuge a wetlands area used by thousands of 
migratory birds and by fish lies behind the state beach there are 
not many migrating birds there this time of year but officials 
fear an invasion of oily water could foul the area for months 
in addition to the 30footwide 2inchthick slick on bolsa 
chica the coast guard said smaller ribbons of oil 4feetwide were 
reported near the huntington beach pier 
cleanup activities at bolsa chica were suspended briefly when 
workers began complaining of headaches and nausea from the oily 
fumes the workers were back on the beach by dawn 
meanwhile there was still no decision on when the 811foot 
