<TEXT>
blacks could hold the key to a resurgent 
buffalo says the author of a study released monday that is billed 
as the most comprehensive ever done of a single black community 
blacks began migrating to buffalo in large numbers around 1940 
just about the time when the citys industries began a slump from 
which they never really recovered said the study conducted by the 
state university of new york at buffalo 
at that point when thousands of new residents were pouring 
into buffalo the citys economy was beginning to change 
researcher henry louis taylor jr told a news conference the 
jobs that lured black people to buffalo were disappearing almost as 
fast as they could get them 
the buffalo labor force is old he said there is no 
population younger than the africanamerican community if you 
train them you solve one of buffalos major problems 
the unemployment rate among blacks in buffalo was 26 percent in 
1940 16 percent in 1960 and 21 percent in 1980 a consistent 8 
percent higher than the citys overall unemployment rate for those 
years said taylor director of sunybuffalos center for applied 
public affairs studies 
the study addresses housing education crime and the quest for 
community among the citys 94262 blacks 
university officials said it was the most comprehensive study 
ever of a single black community the buffalo urban league and the 
common council which commissioned the study plan to use it for a 
range of policy issues 
the report suggests that the east side where 84 percent of 
buffalos black residents live should become one of the citys top 
priorities for economic and social reform before it becomes a 
disaster area like the slums of chicago or detroit 
taylor said city leaders should officially designate the east 
side as a development zone the target of a coordinated effort to 
transform it into a wholesome community or in taylors words a 
renaissance city 
leroy coles the urban leagues president said it will be hard 
to persuade city leaders that the east sides rebirth should be a 
priority 
city hall it seems to me has to become more concerned about 
the growing population suffering from a number of things this 
report speaks to coles said the report is a good way for 
