<TEXT>
soviet leaders called monday for a special session 
of congress to strengthen the office of president a move that 
would solidify mikhail s gorbachevs hold on power 
the development coming on the heels of a landmark communist 
party meeting at which the party agreed to give up its 
constitutional monopoly on power would strengthen the government 
and further erode the party apparatus that has ruled the country 
for 72 years 
gorbachev now holds the offices of party generalsecretary and 
of president the new powers being proposed for the president would 
make it more of a westernstyle office 
tass said the presidium of the supreme soviet the countrys 
highest executive body unanimously favored the establishment of 
democratic presidential power in our country 
the statement did not say whether the president should be 
directly elected by voters but one of gorbachevs key allies on 
the communist party politburo said last week that a nationwide 
popular election might be possible 
foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze speaking at the 
threeday meeting last week of the partys policymaking central 
committee said a new draft of the soviet constitution now being 
written could include direct and general elections for president 
of the country 
gorbachev ducked the question of whether he would run for 
president if the office were up for national balloting 
lets wait and see he told reporters on hand for his 
meeting friday with us secretary of state james a baker iii 
the partys central committee approved the idea of a strong 
presidency at its meeting last week 
but in the text of its new platform released monday night in 
moscow the party leadership left open the question of how the new 
stronger president should be selected 
it said a strong presidency is necesary to ensure stability 
make reforms irreversible make all government institutions 
democratic ensure law and order and represent the soviet union 
abroad 
another key gorbachev ally on the politburo alexander n 
yakovlev said gorbachev was seeking election of a president to a 
fixed term and would empower the president to choose the cabinet 
gorbachev is now serving a fiveyear term as chairman of the 
presidium of the supreme soviet informally referred to as 
president but his real power base remains the party which he 
leads as general secretary but the party post has no certain term 
and in recent weeks party reformers have expressed concern that he 
could be ousted by hardliners opposed to his dramatic reforms 
the party platform called for consolidation of the positions 
and prerogatives of the council of ministers or cabinet but it 
was not clear what would happen to the post of premier that job 
now is held by nikolai i ryzhkov 
the party central committee decision last week cleared the way 
for eventual establishment of opposition political parties the 
party leadership will call on legislators to remove the soviet 
constitutions article 6 which establishes the communist party as 
the leading and guiding force in soviet society 
tass said the presidium headed by gorbachev would ask the 
supreme soviet or legislature to call its 2250member parent 
body the congress of peoples deputies into session in the near 
future no date was proposed 
the supreme soviet reconvenes on wednesday and is likely to 
follow the recommendation of its presidium 
all constitutional questions such as powers of the presidency 
must be decided by the congress which is supposed to meet briefly 
twice a year 
under reforms pushed through by gorbachev in december 1988 the 
president is chosen by the congress 
the presidium said it called for the convening of congress 
because of the debate going on in soviet society about the role of 
the communist party and political reforms 
government leaders want the congress to consider a variety of 
other issues concerning the soviet political system the ownership 
of property and strengthening the soviet government the tass 
report said 
