a manhunt for five men including three 
convicted murderers who escaped from a maximumsecurity state 
prison focused on the chicago area monday 
a sixth escapee was captured late sunday near his cousins home 
in chicago and the five still at large described as extremely 
dangerous were believed to have also headed for the city said 
corrections spokesman nic howell 
the inmates who escaped sunday from the joliet correctional 
facility may have ties to chicago or may simply hope to lose 
themselves in the large metropolitan area he said 
we have no reason to think that these guys are out of state or 
are not in the general vicinity of chicago howell said but 
authorities have no specific leads he said noting the recaptured 
inmate had provided little information 
nothing has panned out yet howell said 
early sunday morning the inmates apparently cut through bars on 
their cells broke a window and cut through bars outside it then 
climbed a low fence and fled the northern illinois prison 
undetected howell said 
about 100 corrections officers and officials were involved in 
the case either helping with the search or the internal 
investigation and security review at the prison 
the prison houses 1300 inmates 500 more than it was intended 
to hold but howell said he didnt know if the crowded conditions 
contributed to the escape 
the six prisoners were last accounted for at 455 am sunday 
the escape was discovered when a headcount came up short at 7 am 
howell said 
the men escaped from segregation cells where they were being 
kept because of disciplinary problems he said four of the men 
were doubled up two to a cell and the other two were alone in 
their cells 
tommy munoz of chicago was captured just after 530 pm sunday 
by prison authorities who had staked out his cousins house on the 
citys southwest side about 40 miles east of the prison howell 
said 
munoz was returned to the joliet where he was serving a 
twoyear sentence for narcotics violations and intimidation the 
spokesman said 
still at large were 
daniel johnson 24 of burns tenn imprisoned for murder 
