<TEXT>
the family of robert schmertz a former owner of 
the boston celtics basketball team has been awarded more than 5 
million because of schmertzs death due to negligence following 
brain surgery 
almost 13 years after the malpractice lawsuit was filed a jury 
in manhattans state supreme court awarded 4 million to schmertzs 
widow phyllis who lives in florida 
the jury also awarded 500000 to each of his two mentally 
handicapped children ronald and jane who live at the woods school 
in langhorne pa and it gave 50000 to his third child nancy 
who lives in manhattan the children are schmertzs from a previous 
marriage 
the award will be paid by columbiapresbyterian hospital where 
schmertz 48 had surgery july 15 1975 for cranial bleeding due 
to a congenital condition said steve mangione spokesman for 
schmertzs lawyer thomas moore 
the hospitals lawyer luke pittoni could not be reached for 
comment monday but mangione said hospital lawyers said they would 
appeal the verdict 
schmertzs operation was a success but the jury found that the 
anesthesiologist dr richard matteo and others were negligent 
because they failed to monitor schmertzs heart and breathing 
properly in the recovery room mangione said 
shortly after entering the recovery room mangione said 
schmertz vomited and aspirated the vomit into his lungs further 
compromising his breathing he lapsed into a coma and died july 23 
eight days later mangione said 
the hospital said it was unable to produce records and xrays 
that documented what happened to schmertz mangione said 
he said moore felt it was more than a coincidence that the two 
crucial xrays and the documentation were missing 
however on the eve of the trial columbiapresbyterian brought 
in a videotape of the schmertz operation which the hospital said 
would show that the surgeon james macmurtrey caused schmertzs 
death mangione said 
but moore observed that the hospital had been using that video 
for 13 years to instruct surgical residents in how to perform 
correctly the procedure done on schmertz 
macmurtrey was eventually removed from the case as a defendant 
the jury ruled friday following a threeweek trial and two days 
of deliberations 
schmertz owned the celtics from 1972 to 1975 mangione said he 
was also a part owner of the hartford whalers and a cofounder of 
the nowdefunct usfl 
</TEXT>
