<TEXT>
honey production dropped 21 percent last year 
to 169 million pounds the agriculture department said monday 
about 33 million colonies produced honey in 1989 a 3 percent 
increase from 1988 according to the annual report but the average 
yield per colony was only 511 pounds down from 663 pounds in 
1988 
adverse conditions were encountered in most states and 
included wet weather restrictions on movement early in the year 
dry weather disease and mite infestations throughout the year 
the report said 
price for the 1989 crop averaged 484 cents per pound down 16 
cents from 1988 the report said 
