cold air began forcing its way into the northwest and the 
northern plains on monday threatening snow and sharply lower 
temperatures but it was good news for coldweary alaska 
alaska has been experiencing severe cold the past couple of 
weeks and a change in the weather pattern across the northern 
hemisphere made alaskas cold air shift toward the lower 48 states 
parts of alaska experienced rapid warming as the cold air began 
leaving with nome reporting a temperature rise of 19 degrees in 21 
minutes during the morning from 25 below zero to 6 below zero 
on the opposite side of the moving air mass temperatures 
dropped during the day in the northern plains and the northern 
rockies at midday cut bank mont reported a temperature of just 
3 degrees above zero and strong northerly wind produced a wind 
chill reading of 39 below 
readings were only in the 20s during the afternoon across parts 
of minnesota wisconsin and michigan 
in the northwest the cold meant snow 
a heavy snow warning was issued for elevations above 500 feet in 
