<TEXT>
a state judge refused monday to drop 64 
million in fines against the united mine workers raising new doubt 
about the future of a tentative settlement by 1700 miners in three 
states 
the strike against pittston coal group spread far beyond that 
one company last summer when thousands of miners staged wildcat 
sympathy strikes 
the umw and pittston reached a tentative agreement jan 1 but 
union leaders said they wouldnt put the contract to a vote of the 
rank and file until all legal action connected with the strike is 
settled 
both the union and the company had asked circuit court judge 
donald mcglothlin to drop the fines but on monday he refused the 
