cape town before taking an evening flight to johannesburg he was 
released unconditionally on sunday 
mandela said negotiations between the anc and the government 
could begin very soon if president fw de klerk continues his 
peace initiative and makes further reforms 
the state of emergency has to be lifted in its entirety and 
political prisoners have to be released mandela told more than 
200 journalists assembled on the lawn outside the official 
residence of anglican archbishop desmond tutu in cape town 
