mexican officials said a weekend aerial 
survey showed low numbers of gray whales arriving in bays along the 
pacific coast of baja california though usbased whalewatchers 
reported were seeing normal numbers 
only about 20 percent of the normal population has arrived 
and were still concerned said ulises cesena montano 
