not have shown up yet ms warhol said adding that weather and 
food supplies can influence migration timing 
cesena said baja california experts speculate that a previously 
unknown cold current called the corriente de la nina might be 
holding up the whales 
the species was once hunted almost to extinction but estimates 
of the total population now run from 17000 to 21000 
