<TEXT>
soviet ambassador yuriy v dubinin said monday 
that the recent historic meeting of the communist party central 
committee has given a powerful political impetus to the soviet 
unions plans for economic restructuring 
dubinin speaking to a business audience about joint ventures in 
the ussr said the committees agreement last week to accept a 
multiparty system and adopt a new platform of reforms would help 
accelerate the countrys economic recovery and expand trade with 
the west 
the soviet unions economic agenda includes taking emergency 
steps to rebuild the economy and laying a foundation for economic 
development dubinin said it also includes creating a legal system 
with laws on property employment and taxes decentralizing the 
economies of republics within the country making the currency 
convertible and reducing foreign debt he said 
however dubinin said the natural mutual attraction between 
the us and soviet business communities could be destroyed by 
the cold war or severe restrictions 
shall we postpone our business interaction until better 
times dubinin asked 
i believe the answer lies in the fact thatwe are already 
experiencing an explosion of interest on the part of american 
businesses toward establishing ties with soviet business 
dubinin underscored the need for a ussoviet trade agreement 
that would relax trade barriers between the two countries and help 
remove obstacles to granting the soviet union mostfavorednation 
trade status a move that could ease the economic troubles under 
which the soviets are living 
top us and soviet trade officials on monday began negotiations 
in washington aimed at reaching a new trade treaty by the time of 
the june summit between soviet president mikhail gorbachev and 
president george bush 
dubinin said more than 1000 joint ventures have been registered 
between soviet and western companies in the last year and more 
than a dozen more joint venture agreements will be signed with 
major american companies in the next few months 
however only about a fifth of those registered have become 
reality due to the structural and economic problems in the soviet 
union 
we are trying to solve those problems dubinin said 
the ambassador said the socalled economic conversion or 
the converting of soviet military plants into facilities for 
manufacturing consumer goods is helping lessen the political 
tension between the soviet union and the west while helping in the 
recovery 
conversion serves to accelerate economic development 
andopens new horizons dubinin said 
dubinin said he returned on sunday from moscow where he 
attended meetings of the communist party central committee and 
meetings with secretary of state james a baker iii that wound up 
saturday 
